Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Agribusiness in conjunction with Bob Jamieson Agencies is pleased to present for sale Inverell Station (the Property). The Property features fertile soils, quality improvements, efficient property layout and secure water sources; offering the complete high-rainfall grazing package in one of Australia's foremost districts.

HOMESTEAD
Inverell Station Homestead features a commanding two-storey brick residence set on an elevated site comprising four large bedrooms, three bathrooms with polished blackbutt timber floors, modern kitchen, open-plan family room, formal lounge and dining rooms, ducted air conditioning and wood fires combine to create a homestead of distinction. Inverell Station Homestead is set in 1.5* hectares stunning tranquil gardens, established trees and sweeping lawns with inground pool, tennis court and two-bedroom guest accommodation.

SCALE
Featuring a total land area of 1,758* hectares of quality soils suited to a range of cropping, fodder production and grazing enterprises showcasing the versatility of the Property.

PRODUCTIVE CABABILITY
In excess of 550* hectares has been sown to forage sorghum and oats which is establishing strongly following recent rainfall allowing a purchaser immediate production options. Historical production of 600* cows and followers with additional backgrounding when seasonal conditions permit

SOILS AND TOPOGRAPHY
Rising from alluvial river flats lining the Macintyre River and Swan Brook Creek through arable slopes comprising black self-mulching basalt soils to lightly timbered hills well suited to a breeding and fattening enterprise.

SECURE WATER SUPPLY
Water for livestock is secured by five* kilometres of Macintyre River and nine* kilometres of Swan Brook Creek frontage. An automated pumping system on the Macintyre River supplies an extensive reticulation system providing secure water availability.

ADDITIONAL ACCOMODATION AND OPERATIONAL IMPROVEMENTS
An additional historic four-bedroom homestead once owned by the founder of Inverell and additional managers residence provides alternative accommodation options for owners or staff. Operational improvements include three machinery sheds and two sets of steel cattle yards.

CLIMATE AND LOCATION
Located within the Northern Tablelands Region of New South Wales, five* linear kilometres north of Inverell providing potential subdivision options (subject to council approval).
The strategic location of the Property provides convenient access to a full range of markets, services and amenities.

Northern Tablelands is considered the premier grazing region of New South Wales, a deserved recognition on account of reliable, temperate climate

THE OFFERING
Inverell Station is offered for sale by Expression of Interest in-one-line or as separate assets closing Wednesday 8 April 2020 at 4.00pm Australian Eastern Daylight Time (AEDT). The individual offerings are outlined below:

Lot One: Inverell Station Homestead â€“ Featuring two* hectares including the notable Inverell Station Homestead and gardens.

Lot Two: Inverell Station - Comprises 1,596* hectares quality soils featuring operational improvements and historic homestead built by the districts first settler. Double-frontage to Macintyre River and Swan Brook. Potential subdivision options (subject to council approval).

Lot Three: Inverell Station Homestead Block - Comprises 160* hectares of river flats with an exceptional four-bedroom brick veneer residence. Features three* kilometre frontage to the Macintyre River.

Expression of Interest has been extended due to travel restrictions.
